X_1, \dots, X_n
k
p
P(X_k = k|k,p) = \binom{k}{x}p^{x}(1-p)^{k-x}
k
p
kp(1-p)+k^{2}p^{2}
\bar{X} = kp
\frac{1}{n} \sum X_{i}^{2} = kp(1-p)+k^{2}p^{2}
X_i
\sum_{j=0}^k Y_{i,j}
Y_{i,j}
1
p
0
1-p
E[Y_{i,j}]=p
E[Y_{i,j}^2]=p
E[\left(Y_{i,j}-E[Y_{i,j}]\right)^2]=E[Y_{i,j}^2]-E[Y_{i,j}]^2 =p - p^2 = p(1-p)
E[X_{i}]=\sum_{j=0}^k E[Y_{i,j}]=kp
E[\left(X_{i}-E[X_{i}]\right)^2]=\sum_{j=0}^k E[\left(Y_{i,j}-E[Y_{i,j}]\right)^2]=kp(1-p).
E[X_{i}^2]=E[\left(X_{i}-E[X_{i}]\right)^2] + E[X_{i}]^2 = kp(1-p) + k^2 p^2
E\left[ \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^n X_i^2 \right] = \frac{1}{n} E\left[  \sum_{i=1}^n \left(kp(1-p) + k^2 p^2\right) \right] = kp(1-p) + k^2 p^2
